@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowThickness 1.5
    ArrowColor #333333
    LifeLineBorderColor #777777
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
    ParticipantBorderColor #555555
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
    GroupBorderColor #888888
    GroupBodyBackgroundColor #F9F9F9
    DividerBackgroundColor #E8EAF6
    DividerBorderColor #9FA8DA
}
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam noteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EDE7F6
skinparam actorBorderColor #7E57C2
skinparam roundcorner 8

title **SEC-05 · Scenario 01: Expired Password → Token Issued**\n<size:12>AC: "Expired password triggers token issuance"</size>

actor      "User\n(Browser)"                                    as User
participant "API Gateway\n<size:10>/auth/login</size>"          as API   #E3F2FD
participant "Auth Orchestrator\n<size:10>(New Service)</size>"           as Orch  #EDE7F6
participant "User Service"                                       as SVC   #E8F5E9
database   "User DB"                                             as DB    #F1F8E9
database   "Redis\n<size:10>TTL Store</size>"                    as Redis #FFF3E0
participant "Notification Service\n<size:10>(Microservice/TCP)</size>" as Notif #FCE4EC
participant "Amazon SES\n<size:10>(SMTP)</size>"                        as SES   #FFF8E1

== 1. Login & Pre-checks ==

User -> API  : POST /auth/login\n{ email, password }

API  -> Orch : login({ email, password })

Orch -> SVC  : find_user_by_email(email)

group User Lookup
    SVC -> DB   : SELECT id, is_email_verified,\n  password_hash,\n  password_voided_at, password_changed_at\nFROM users\nWHERE email = ?\nAND deleted_at IS NULL\nAND password_voided_at IS NULL
    note right of DB
        password_voided_at, password_changed_at
        ⚠ new columns — migration required
        ---
        "voided" = password_voided_at IS NOT NULL
        Anti-spam: once token issued, password_voided_at is set
        → subsequent login attempts return 401 immediately
        → no duplicate emails possible
    end note
    DB --> SVC  : user row | null
end

SVC --> Orch : { id, is_email_verified,\n  password_hash,\n  password_voided_at,\n  password_changed_at }\n| RpcException(404)

alt user not found | not email verified | voided | wrong password
    Orch --> API  : 401 Generic login failure
    API  --> User : 401 Generic login failure
end

Orch -> Orch : bcrypt.compare(password, password_hash) OK\ndays_since_change = NOW() - password_changed_at > 90 → EXPIRED

== 2. Token Generation ==

Orch -> Orch : raw_token  = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex')\ntoken_hash = SHA-256(raw_token)

Orch -> Redis : SET expired_reset:{token_hash} = user_id  EX 900
Redis --> Orch : OK

Orch -> SVC  : UPDATE user\n  password_voided_at     = NOW()\n  password_reset_issued_at = NOW()
SVC  --> Orch : updated

== 3. Notify User ==

Orch ->> Notif : emit('send_password_expiry_email')\n{ to: user.email,\n  reset_url: https://<domain>/auth/expired-reset?token=<raw_token> }

note right of Notif
    Fire-and-forget (@EventPattern).
    ⚠ Not yet implemented — new handler + template needed.
    Parallel to send_invitation_email pattern.
    raw_token in reset_url only — never in logs.
end note

Notif -> Notif : render password-expiry template\n{ reset_url, year }

Notif -> SES  : nodemailer.sendMail() via SMTP\n{ from: "Zimple Solution <no-reply@...>",\n  to, subject, html, text }
SES --> Notif : SMTP 250 OK (accepted)

Orch --> API  : 200 "Your password has expired.\nWe've sent a login link to your email."
API  --> User : 200 "Your password has expired.\nWe've sent a login link to your email."

@enduml
